      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's what people always say, but it doesn't feel real. It feels like the walls are closing in. Even when I'm alone, I can still hear them. It's not just anxiety, it's like... I've already lost. There's no point in trying to \"take a step back\" because there's nowhere to go where they won't find a way to make me feel small. It's just constant. I feel so heavy and tired of fighting something that I can't even win. Everything just feels so hollow.",
